The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | HDIL profit falls
                                                                                                               HDIL profit falls
                            
	Mumbai, May 23 (PTI): Housing Development amp; Infrastructure Ltd (HDIL) today said its net profit for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2009 had declined 91.25 per cent to Rs 61.92 crore from Rs 708.24 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.        
	For the year ended March 31, the company had a consolidated net profit of Rs 786.53 crore, down 77.05 per cent, from Rs 3,427.23 crore in the same period a year ago.        
	The company said its board had approved to raise $600 million (around Rs 28,31.70 crore) from qualified institutional buyers by issuing shares on a preferential basis. The board also decided to make preferential allotment of warrants to the promoter of the company.        
	NTPC net        
	State-run National Thermal Power Corporation has reported a 57.77 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 2,113.35 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2009 against Rs 1,339.48 crore in the same quarter a year ago. Net sales of the company rose to Rs 11,445.78 crore for the quarter under review from Rs 10,743.59 crore in the same quarter ended March 2008.                                                                                                                                        
